cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) and specifically focuses on deep input linearization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves predicting function words, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a shared task, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
